sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as Trader
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant API as Order Controller
    participant OS as OrderService
    participant MD as MarketDataService
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant W as Limit Worker (every 30s)

    Note over U,FE: Phase 1 - Order Placement
    U->>FE: Submit LIMIT BUY @ $60000
    FE->>API: POST /api/orders {type:LIMIT, side:BUY, qty, price:60000}
    API->>OS: createOrder()
    OS->>MD: getCoin(coinId)
    MD-->>OS: current_price = $65000
    OS->>OS: shouldFill(BUY, 60000, 65000) - false
    OS->>DB: Order.create(status=PENDING, price=60000)
    OS-->>API: pending order
    API-->>FE: 201 {order: PENDING}
    FE-->>U: "Emir bekliyor"

    Note over W,DB: Phase 2 - Background Matching (loop every 30s)
    loop every 30 seconds
        W->>OS: processPendingLimitOrders()
        OS->>DB: find {status:PENDING, type:LIMIT}
        DB-->>OS: pending orders[]

        OS->>MD: getPriceMap(coinIds)
        MD-->>OS: {bitcoin: 59800, ...}

        loop for each pending order
            alt expiresAt passed
                OS->>DB: Order.update(status=EXPIRED)
            else shouldFill(side, limit, market)
                OS->>OS: _executeOrder(order, marketPrice)
                Note over OS,DB: Same flow as Market order:<br/>cash--, asset++, Transaction created
                OS->>DB: Order.update(status=FILLED)
            else not yet
                Note over OS: skip, check next cycle
            end
        end
    end

    Note over U,FE: Phase 3 - User checks status
    U->>FE: Open Orders page
    FE->>API: GET /api/orders
    API-->>FE: orders[] including FILLED ones
    FE-->>U: Order shown as FILLED with executedPrice
